mistral.reason: Hangin' Around is a song released by Grover Windham in 2023, not an album. Re-Entry is a second album released by UK R&B/hip-hop collective Big Brovaz in 2007.

gemma2.reason: Multiple sources clearly state that "Hangin' Around" is a song by Eric Church, and possibly also Grover Windham, while Re-Entry is an album by the UK R&B/hip-hop collective Big Brovaz.

llama3.1.reason: The album of Hangin' Around mentioned in the context information (4) is a single by Edgar Winter, not Re-Entry which is an album by Big Brovaz.

qwen2.5.reason: The context mentions "Hangin' Around" as a title track from Eric Church's upcoming album Desperate Man, not from an album called Re-Entry. Additionally, Re-Entry is described as the second album released by Big Brovaz.
